From: Abel Vesa <abel.vesa@nxp.com>
Date: Sun, 23 Dec 2018 07:08:31 +0000
Subject: pinctrl: freescale: Break dependency on SOC_IMX8MQ for i.MX8MQ
Git-commit: b09f629ce36d94381f96a03ea1507861d1d5de3b
Patch-mainline: v5.0-rc1
References: FATE#324492

The CONFIG_SOC_IMX8MQ will go away, so the dependency can be based on
ARCH_MXC && ARM64.

Signed-off-by: Abel Vesa <abel.vesa@nxp.com>
Acked-by: Dong Aisheng <aisheng.dong@nxp.com>
Reviewed-by: Fabio Estevam <festevam@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Linus Walleij <linus.walleij@linaro.org>
Acked-by: Nicolas Saenz Julienne <nsaenzjulienne@suse.de>
---
 drivers/pinctrl/freescale/Kconfig | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/pinctrl/freescale/Kconfig b/drivers/pinctrl/freescale/Kconfig
index d20ae4b7f996..72b869d888e2 100644
--- a/drivers/pinctrl/freescale/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/pinctrl/freescale/Kconfig
@@ -124,7 +124,7 @@ config PINCTRL_IMX7ULP
 
 config PINCTRL_IMX8MQ
 	bool "IMX8MQ pinctrl driver"
-	depends on SOC_IMX8MQ
+	depends on ARCH_MXC && ARM64
 	select PINCTRL_IMX
 	help
 	  Say Y here to enable the imx8mq pinctrl driver

